WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:02.773
I always hate seeing myself on the screen.

00:03.274 --> 00:03.794
It's gross.

00:04.355 --> 00:08.021
You know, it's like when you hear your own voice sometimes, I don't sound like that, do I?

00:08.041 --> 00:08.722
That is awful.

00:08.782 --> 00:09.443
How does that happen?

00:10.284 --> 00:11.566
That's where it's like, whenever you go, don't do that.

00:12.087 --> 00:12.387
Come back.

00:13.309 --> 00:16.353
Yeah, that's where it's like when you see yourself on the screen.

00:16.994 --> 00:21.481
Also, on there, I had slightly, very slightly longer, tufti hair.

00:22.102 --> 00:23.243
Every now and again, I buzz it off.

00:23.404 --> 00:27.730
And my mum, who watches at home, my mum, she

00:28.066 --> 00:31.750
said to me the other day, sent me a message saying, hey, Pete, what's happened to your lovely blonde hair?

00:32.992 --> 00:34.934
He's like, where have you been, mama?

00:35.495 --> 00:37.037
She said, no, but you've taken so much off.

00:37.057 --> 00:38.078
You haven't got any at all.

00:38.098 --> 00:39.399
I was like, no, it's just the lights.

00:41.442 --> 00:41.782
Maybe.

00:42.283 --> 00:42.643
OK.

00:44.305 --> 00:44.425
Right.

00:44.445 --> 00:55.218
We are looking at the theme at the moment of stepping into the story and how we can step into the story that God is writing in Skylot Church and wherever God has placed us.

00:55.490 --> 00:56.451
out into the world.

00:56.752 --> 01:01.257
It's so important that it's not just for here, but it's everywhere, stepping into the story.

01:02.058 --> 01:07.686
And this week, one week ahead of Giving Sunday, as you just heard, we're going to take a look at giving.

01:08.627 --> 01:12.852
And giving is something that we, I'm talking actually cash here, I'm talking about money.

01:13.273 --> 01:17.458
And it's something we don't talk about loads in this church.

01:18.370 --> 01:22.154
if you are tuning in for the first time at home, or this is your first time into church.

01:23.595 --> 01:25.117
You've come and they're talking about church.

01:25.157 --> 01:26.478
Don't worry about money.

01:26.698 --> 01:30.703
We're not raising money for the roof campaign, which would be what most churches seem to be doing.

01:30.763 --> 01:39.191
But we do need, occasionally, to talk about money because we just said, Jesus, take your place at the center, at the center of our lives.

01:39.311 --> 01:44.156
And sometimes other things can creep their way into what is the most important thing in our lives.

01:44.677 --> 01:45.938
And so we're gonna talk about,

01:46.146 --> 01:50.453
giving financially this morning ahead of giving Sunday next week.

01:51.475 --> 01:54.480
I know that there are loads of ways that we can give.

01:54.500 --> 02:09.906
Please, I'm not belittling any other way of giving, but sometimes we can say we can give our money or we could give our time or we can give our energy or our prayer and we kind of pick the ones that we like the most and

02:10.658 --> 02:14.222
Therefore, we can say, well, I don't give money, but what I do do is this.

02:14.342 --> 02:18.027
But actually, it's not really an either or I want to speak about today.

02:18.047 --> 02:19.448
It's an and both.

02:20.289 --> 02:25.516
Here's a trigger warning for you because some of you are already triggered and already feeling, don't like this at all.

02:26.156 --> 02:27.398
I don't like it.

02:27.418 --> 02:30.882
There's something about money that can make a squirm more than most other things.

02:32.624 --> 02:37.650
There's something about our bank balance and me talking about it that gives you the ick.

02:38.210 --> 02:43.679
There's something about a 52-year-old man on the platform saying, ick, that gives some of you the ick.

02:49.068 --> 02:58.002
If I put out a little health check question and said, even in your close-up friendship groups, how comfy are you about telling your best friends how much you earn?

02:58.146 --> 02:59.168
Most people don't.

02:59.248 --> 03:03.995
For some reason, I think it's the best kept secret in the country, even from our closest, nearest and dearest.

03:04.335 --> 03:05.597
We don't talk about what we earn.

03:05.898 --> 03:09.523
There's something about it that's really quite private and boxed in.

03:09.623 --> 03:13.749
And I'm not suggesting that you will start standing up and shouting out how much you earn.

03:13.789 --> 03:14.671
That's not what I'm saying.

03:15.292 --> 03:27.730
But I do believe that there can be a cultural thing about money that keeps it so private, keeps it so it's mine, and it's for me and mine, that it can make us uncomfortable when it's spoken about.

03:27.874 --> 03:37.686
So I want to challenge you, as I've been challenged myself in the past, that if you feel that a drawbridge is starting to come up as I speak, and the portcullis is coming down, and you're hoping this will be over soon.

03:38.507 --> 03:40.690
Let's just pray about that for a moment.

03:40.710 --> 03:41.851
And allow God to speak to us.

03:42.092 --> 03:45.556
I don't want to influence anybody in their money.

03:45.676 --> 03:46.978
I don't want to do that.

03:47.018 --> 03:57.010
But what I do want to do today is to speak a little bit and to teach a little bit about what the Bible says, about tithing and about offerings, and what we do with our money.

03:57.250 --> 04:02.617
If you are feeling like, I don't like it at all, then you're in good company because there's this cool story.

04:02.638 --> 04:10.208
Oh, by the way, look, there's a piggy bank sort of thing, but we were thinking of putting this slide up because it can be a sacred cow, but we're not going there.

04:10.228 --> 04:14.414
So we're going to do, we're going to do this instead.

04:15.095 --> 04:16.196
We're going to look at this little verse.

04:16.236 --> 04:25.970
If you feel a bit downhearted by this look, as Jesus was starting out on his way to Jerusalem, a man came running up to him, knelt down and asked, good teacher, what must I do to inherit eternal life?

04:26.498 --> 04:28.180
Why'd you call me good, Jesus asked?

04:28.500 --> 04:40.652
Only God is truly good, but to answer your question, you know the commandments, you must not murder, you mustn't commit adultery, you must not steal, you must not testify falsely, you mustn't cheat anyone, honor your father and mother.

04:40.692 --> 04:45.016
Teacher, the young man replied, I've obeyed all these commandments since I was young.

04:46.157 --> 04:49.400
Looking at the man, Jesus felt genuine love for him.

04:50.061 --> 04:55.186
There is still one thing you haven't done, he told him, go and sell all your possessions.

04:55.394 --> 04:56.876
and give the money to the poor.

04:57.437 --> 04:59.179
And you will have treasure in heaven.

04:59.700 --> 05:01.382
Then come and follow me.

05:02.123 --> 05:05.628
And just like many of us, this, the man's face fell.

05:06.249 --> 05:09.353
And he went away sad, for he had many possessions.

05:13.378 --> 05:16.422
This passage, this story, isn't saying is you can't have wealth.

05:17.944 --> 05:21.709
But the problem is that so often our wealth has us.

05:21.730 --> 05:25.074
It's okay to have money as long as money doesn't have you.

05:25.314 --> 05:30.701
It's okay to have money in your back pocket as long as you are not in the back pocket of the money that you have.

05:31.502 --> 05:33.105
Having money is never the issue.

05:34.106 --> 05:36.890
I've got a salary, I've got a pension, I've got life insurance.

05:37.430 --> 05:43.058
The issue is the importance that I place on that money and what I'm prepared to allow God to do with it.

05:43.879 --> 05:49.907
And every week in this church, you hear the phrase as you heard this morning, we're now going to take up our tithes and offerings.

05:51.449 --> 05:53.292
We do it as an extension of our worship.

05:53.933 --> 05:54.994
It was said this morning,

05:55.714 --> 06:01.600
You then may see a QR code behind us on the screen, and then you're encouraged to say hello to somebody near to you.

06:02.141 --> 06:08.848
And this kind of downplaying of giving has actually done you guys a disservice, I think.

06:08.868 --> 06:10.951
Because we don't like to talk much about money.

06:10.991 --> 06:13.914
It makes us feel awkward too, as the leaders.

06:13.974 --> 06:15.455
And so sometimes we sort of downplay it.

06:15.475 --> 06:16.717
Like, it's time for the offerings.

06:16.957 --> 06:18.959
Hey, why don't you say hello to somebody near to you?

06:20.621 --> 06:25.266
Recently, more than one of the staff and the leadership team have been asked what tithes and offerings are.

06:25.826 --> 06:28.950
I actually haven't spoken on what tithes and offerings are since 2016.

06:29.210 --> 06:33.395
Ten years since I've devoted a message to it.

06:33.415 --> 06:36.018
So if this is your first time, it has been ten years.

06:36.659 --> 06:37.480
It's not every week.

06:39.722 --> 06:45.249
And you could really well be forgiven that into thinking that tithing is about being welcoming to others.

06:46.670 --> 06:48.072
It's time for our tithes and offerings.

06:48.132 --> 06:51.035
Why don't you say hello to somebody sitting near you and make them feel welcome?

06:51.556 --> 06:53.298
The two things seem to go hand in hand.

06:55.106 --> 06:59.656
Another member of staff recently was asked, who funds all this stuff?

06:59.676 --> 07:02.021
Who funds everything that goes on in this building?

07:02.803 --> 07:03.865
Who funds the staff?

07:04.487 --> 07:07.393
Who funds everything that you do here and out into the world?

07:08.576 --> 07:11.442
Remember Vision Sunday on the 11th of Jan.

07:12.258 --> 07:14.843
Remember everything, if you haven't heard it, go back and have a listen.

07:14.863 --> 07:16.847
There's so much that's happening in the life of the church.

07:16.927 --> 07:34.642
Everything we do with our preschoolers, our kids, our youth, everything we do with discipleship, when we gather our pastoral care, looking after this building, baptizing, dedicating, eating together, cooking over a thousand meals for the community last year, making hundreds of hampers, reaching 255

07:34.722 --> 07:46.194
250 girls in five high schools with a self-esteem course, supporting students in Chompsford College, working with and supporting over 50 domestic abuse survivors, working into the...

07:46.306 --> 08:01.148
prison on many occasions, more than once every week of the year, providing health care for the homeless, having a bursary fund for primary schools in this area so that people who can't afford uniform and school trips can apply to us, and we will buy their school uniforms.

08:01.188 --> 08:05.554
We've also bought washing machines and all sorts of things for families in need in the community.

08:06.055 --> 08:11.443
Who is it who just managed to buy a cow in Romania called Sky with big love?

08:12.424 --> 08:13.586
How does it all happen?

08:13.730 --> 08:15.452
How is this stuff funded?

08:15.833 --> 08:18.516
And the answer is, is funded by us.

08:19.818 --> 08:20.338
We fund it.

08:21.360 --> 08:26.146
We haven't had any external funding beyond like a £5,000 pot for a few years now.

08:26.266 --> 08:31.853
We fund all of the stuff that is going on through our tithes and our offerings.

08:31.913 --> 08:35.037
So this morning, we're going to have a look at what both of those words are.

08:35.057 --> 08:35.658
What are tithes?

08:35.978 --> 08:36.820
What are offerings?

08:37.140 --> 08:38.702
So, tithing.

08:40.264 --> 08:41.906
A tithe means a tenth.

08:42.018 --> 08:50.311
First of all, that's the definition or that's the sort of where the word comes from.

08:50.331 --> 08:51.873
A tithe means a tenth.

08:52.754 --> 08:54.857
It first appears in Genesis chapter 14.

08:56.119 --> 09:02.809
What happens here is that Abraham, who later will be called Abraham, had separated from his nephew Lot.

09:03.250 --> 09:11.122
They were in good relationship with each other, but the Bible says they've got so many herds, so many flocks, that the land cannot sustain

09:11.330 --> 09:15.516
both of those groups of the family together and all of their livestock.

09:16.237 --> 09:22.846
And so what happens is that Abraham and Lot, they separate and go different ways, but still in good relationship.

09:22.866 --> 09:26.130
Then a war breaks out in the area that Lot has gone to.

09:26.531 --> 09:31.698
And as part of the spoils of the war, Lot and his family and all of their belongings have been captured.

09:32.194 --> 09:34.777
Abraham, sorry, hears about this.

09:35.298 --> 09:40.825
And he executes a mission to go and rescue Lot, his family and their possessions and bring them all back.

09:40.905 --> 09:41.786
And he's successful.

09:42.827 --> 09:49.475
And when he comes back, the king of Salem, which would become Jerusalem, appears.

09:52.519 --> 09:53.460
And this is what it says.

09:54.662 --> 09:58.367
Then Melchizedek, king of Salem, brought out bread and wine.

09:59.127 --> 10:01.170
He was priest of God most high.

10:01.602 --> 10:06.067
And he blessed Abraham, saying, blessed be Abraham by God most high, creator of heaven and earth.

10:06.648 --> 10:10.192
And praise be to God most high, who delivered your enemies into your hands.

10:10.933 --> 10:13.716
Then Abraham gave him a tenth of everything.

10:15.398 --> 10:22.346
As you study the Bible and you read around this, Melchizedek is a really interesting character.

10:22.426 --> 10:25.650
And many see him as a forerunner of Jesus.

10:25.858 --> 10:30.605
if not Jesus himself, but a forerunner in the likeness of Jesus.

10:30.665 --> 10:31.427
And here he is.

10:31.547 --> 10:34.651
He is the king of Salem, the king of Jerusalem.

10:34.912 --> 10:37.816
And I love the fact he comes out with bread and wine.

10:37.977 --> 10:41.662
I'm sure there must be some symbolism there that's really important.

10:41.903 --> 10:44.146
He was priest of God most high.

10:44.246 --> 10:47.511
This was a forerunner of Jesus himself.

10:47.812 --> 10:49.474
And how did Abraham respond?

10:49.574 --> 10:52.018
He gave him a tenth of everything.

10:52.770 --> 10:55.052
So the tithe began as an act of worship.

10:55.112 --> 10:58.796
It began as gratitude to God through the high priest.

10:59.237 --> 11:02.480
Not because he had to, not because he was told to.

11:02.520 --> 11:09.207
Not because he was told that if you join this church, you have to sign on this dotted line and give 10% of your income.

11:09.607 --> 11:13.691
Now this first ever tithe was a freely given act of worship.

11:14.392 --> 11:20.338
And 14 chapters later, Abraham's grandson, Jacob, does something similar.

11:20.738 --> 11:22.260
He encounters God in a dream.

11:22.300 --> 11:24.663
If you've read it, there's this ladder that's going on.

11:24.763 --> 11:27.667
And Jacob has promised many things.

11:28.648 --> 11:41.664
And he says this, if God will be with me and will watch over me on this journey I am taking and will give me food to eat and clothes to wear so that I return safely to my father's household, then the Lord will be my God.

11:42.164 --> 11:45.449
And this stone that I have set up as a pillar will be God's house.

11:46.390 --> 11:49.874
And of all that you give me, I will give you a tenth.

11:51.042 --> 11:57.730
Once again, not because of law, but because of an act of worship and an act of gratitude to God.

11:58.571 --> 12:08.943
Now, later on in the book of Leviticus, this does become a written law for the people of God that a tithe of everything belongs to the Lord and should be brought to the Lord.

12:10.365 --> 12:14.930
And this would be used to support the work of the tabernacle.

12:15.170 --> 12:20.336
where God dwelt by specifically giving to the priests and the Levites as they went about their duties.

12:20.777 --> 12:24.842
If you fast forward, there's so much that could be said, but time won't be with us if we do.

12:24.862 --> 12:30.269
If we fast forward to the end of the Old Testament, the last book, you'll find this.

12:31.931 --> 12:36.256
Bring all the tithes into the storehouse, so there will be enough food in my temple.

12:37.177 --> 12:41.202
If you do, says the Lord of Heaven's armies, I will open the windows of heaven for you.

12:41.698 --> 12:45.904
I will pour out a blessing so great you won't have enough room to take it in.

12:46.905 --> 12:48.087
Put me to the test."

12:49.629 --> 12:51.972
Interesting.

12:51.992 --> 12:57.540
When Nick and I joined this church, we used to distribute our tithe across loads of organizations.

12:58.321 --> 13:02.227
So we understood about giving a tenth, but we give 2% there and 1% there.

13:02.627 --> 13:03.989
And we used to do it all across.

13:04.049 --> 13:04.850
We'd divide it up.

13:05.531 --> 13:10.258
And then we were challenged by Steve Crouch, who was the worship pastor here at the time.

13:10.434 --> 13:17.641
He spoke to us about bringing it to the storehouse based on what I've shared with you this morning, the place where you get fed spiritually.

13:18.422 --> 13:20.885
We looked into it, we weren't beating over the head.

13:21.305 --> 13:25.109
We looked into it, we prayed into it, and we decided, yep, that's what we'd like to do.

13:25.489 --> 13:31.455
Not because we were forced or cajoled, and you must be getting that from me, hopefully, I'm not trying to force or cajole anybody.

13:32.196 --> 13:38.162
But because we were convinced personally, and so we have been tithing into this storehouse for the past 25 years,

13:38.690 --> 13:43.035
bringing a minimum of 10% of everything we have to this church.

13:43.916 --> 13:50.483
I find it really interesting that the verse above, the verse behind me says, put me to the test.

13:51.384 --> 13:53.926
Because that's not something we're encouraged to do generally.

13:53.966 --> 14:04.518
And actually, most of us will know that when Jesus is in the desert in Matthew 4, he quotes Deuteronomy 6 to the enemy and says, you should not put the Lord your God to the test.

14:05.719 --> 14:06.159
We know that.

14:06.740 --> 14:08.562
But here, there is a specific

14:08.674 --> 14:12.077
instance where it is permitted, even encouraged by God.

14:12.638 --> 14:13.279
Read through it again.

14:14.660 --> 14:15.701
We're encouraged to do it.

14:16.462 --> 14:18.063
This isn't prosperity teaching.

14:18.944 --> 14:21.427
It doesn't mean you give God 10 pounds, he'll give you 20.

14:21.487 --> 14:25.731
It's not like the best investment plan you can ever come up with for your money to make good money.

14:26.532 --> 14:30.175
Because when God says he blesses you, he blesses you how he sees fit to bless you.

14:30.556 --> 14:33.739
You may hope he blesses you with money, but he may bless you in other ways.

14:35.000 --> 14:36.882
He chooses how he does that.

14:37.250 --> 14:41.635
We mustn't give to Him so that we receive in all the areas we've got listed.

14:43.497 --> 14:46.560
We give to Him knowing that He is generous and wants to bless us.

14:47.642 --> 14:58.474
I've spoken to so many people who have been, who have got stories about God, how God has done miracles with their 90% when they faithfully tithe their 10%.

14:58.574 --> 15:06.002
And for the sake of balance, I know many people who don't tithe and they're still blessed by God because our God is awesome and loving and generous and blooming brilliant.

15:06.946 --> 15:09.789
But here it says, I will open the windows of heaven for you.

15:10.190 --> 15:13.874
I will pour out a blessing so great you won't have enough room to take it in.

15:14.314 --> 15:14.795
Try it.

15:15.456 --> 15:16.917
Put me to the test.

15:17.258 --> 15:18.079
Seems pretty clear.

15:19.120 --> 15:25.067
One of the things that can be really tricky for us when it comes to money is the phrase, it's mine.

15:27.069 --> 15:27.489
It's mine.

15:29.251 --> 15:29.712
I earned it.

15:30.433 --> 15:31.474
I can do what I want with it.

15:32.034 --> 15:34.919
I remember when I got paid from, you know, my early paper rounds.

15:35.399 --> 15:37.222
I finally had some money, not much.

15:37.323 --> 15:38.625
I was absolutely ripped off.

15:38.925 --> 15:40.067
We were talking about this the other day.

15:40.087 --> 15:40.848
£3.60.

15:40.868 --> 15:44.434
£3.60 a week.

15:44.454 --> 15:45.055
Six days.

15:45.075 --> 15:47.820
60 per day, honestly.

15:48.341 --> 15:49.002
Took me an hour.

15:51.566 --> 15:54.130
Some people, they're lucky enough I do the road next to the

15:54.306 --> 15:57.730
news agent, you know, every house has a paper and they've done one road and they go home.

15:58.070 --> 15:59.872
Mine, I had every distant house.

16:00.293 --> 16:01.955
I went and my dad to be fair.

16:02.215 --> 16:03.556
We went on our bikes, thanks dad.

16:03.857 --> 16:05.619
We went on our bikes and we would deliver these stuff.

16:05.739 --> 16:06.480
Absolutely ripped off.

16:06.560 --> 16:12.366
But I knew that when I got that money, it was mine and I remember when I then got my Saturday job and it was mine and I could finally buy a curry.

16:12.887 --> 16:13.708
Praise the Lord.

16:14.449 --> 16:17.532
Because my dad didn't like all that foreign muck, you know, that's what he used to say.

16:18.213 --> 16:20.055
So I'd go out and I'd go for it.

16:20.075 --> 16:21.036
I'm getting a calmer.

16:21.056 --> 16:22.738
I'm going to spend half my money.

16:23.746 --> 16:25.348
It was a curry to me, trust me.

16:27.370 --> 16:30.574
I only ate sausages, chips, and beans, so a cormor was pretty amazing.

16:32.977 --> 16:34.179
But anyway, that was my point.

16:34.259 --> 16:34.900
My point is this.

16:35.561 --> 16:37.183
I'd been paid, and finally it was mine.

16:37.823 --> 16:40.967
And I finally could do what I wanted with it, and no one can tell me what to do with it.

16:41.768 --> 16:43.270
And we can still be like that as grown-ups.

16:44.972 --> 16:45.653
This is mine.

16:45.673 --> 16:53.042
The problem with this is mine is, you know, it could become a bit like

16:53.250 --> 16:56.494
golem.

16:56.514 --> 16:59.557
As the journey progresses, it's mine, my own.

17:00.198 --> 17:00.938
Somebody's got the voice.

17:01.058 --> 17:01.659
Somebody can do it.

17:02.440 --> 17:06.504
It's like, that's how we can be.

17:06.544 --> 17:11.189
Please talk to me about the serving in the life of the church.

17:11.910 --> 17:19.058
I'd rather go up and listen to your hundredth response of the year on kids' church than have you talk about my money.

17:20.258 --> 17:21.119
I wish I could do it.

17:21.239 --> 17:21.860
It'd be so good.

17:21.880 --> 17:23.782
I should have practiced, but I didn't.

17:24.583 --> 17:24.763
Sorry.

17:25.024 --> 17:26.185
This was helpful for us.

17:27.547 --> 17:28.848
Bring all the tithes.

17:30.330 --> 17:30.671
Bring.

17:31.011 --> 17:35.156
That verb is a really useful verb for me because it doesn't say pay.

17:37.018 --> 17:38.140
It doesn't say pay.

17:38.600 --> 17:41.804
Heaven forbid that it said pay because this is not a tax.

17:42.785 --> 17:44.427
We are not paying a tax to God.

17:45.068 --> 17:45.829
It's not a debt.

17:45.949 --> 17:48.092
It's not a stranglehold over our lives.

17:49.013 --> 17:50.034
We don't pay it.

17:50.562 --> 17:52.466
It doesn't even say, give.

17:53.448 --> 17:54.369
I find that interesting.

17:55.071 --> 17:59.319
Because giving comes with offerings that we're going to look at in just a sec.

17:59.339 --> 18:00.341
This is God's being.

18:01.123 --> 18:02.305
It says, bring.

18:03.647 --> 18:06.573
And this has helped frame our thinking on tithing.

18:07.455 --> 18:08.357
This is God's being.

18:08.417 --> 18:11.122
Imagine I give my daughters 10 pounds each.

18:11.714 --> 18:13.898
And I say, girls, I'm going to give you a tenor each.

18:14.178 --> 18:18.305
What I want you to do is to bring one pound of that and put it into the family pot.

18:18.826 --> 18:21.931
Then you are free to do with whatever you like with the other nine pounds.

18:23.273 --> 18:23.553
Okay?

18:23.613 --> 18:30.524
And you can choose to be generous with that and give some of that away if you want to, but make sure you bring the one pound into the family pot, into the middle.

18:31.907 --> 18:33.810
That's the way we view tithing.

18:34.631 --> 18:38.898
That whatever God gives us, the first 10% we bring to Him.

18:39.202 --> 18:43.609
And we can joyfully and excitedly bring it to him so that his kingdom can be built.

18:43.949 --> 18:49.138
And we can continue as a church to do all of those things I spoke about earlier on.

18:50.660 --> 18:54.186
This 10% thing is often tied in with a phrase called first fruits.

18:54.766 --> 19:01.778
Haven't got time to go back into all of that, but it goes back as far as Genesis 4 actually with the cane and able and the gifts that they gave.

19:02.719 --> 19:07.186
I can go into, I'm fascinated by it and I'll talk to you about it if you like.

19:07.426 --> 19:11.333
On a practical level, what does it mean for us to give first fruits?

19:12.194 --> 19:17.703
Well, basically that means giving it the beginning of the month rather than the end.

19:17.723 --> 19:23.974
Notoriously, if we plan to give God 10% at the end of the month, there's not much left to play with.

19:24.094 --> 19:30.605
I mean, how many of us are desperately waiting for payday to come around, especially on the month like January, when it goes on forever?

19:30.905 --> 19:32.768
And we've had Christmas like, when is payday?

19:32.788 --> 19:33.810
It must be coming soon.

19:34.370 --> 19:38.177
first fruits is giving to God from the beginning of what we get, not the end.

19:38.738 --> 19:47.174
And again, just for transparency's sake, not because Nick and I are heroes, there are loads of people doing this, but just so you know, the way we give our first fruits and our tithe is quite straightforward.

19:47.716 --> 19:50.561
We look at our annual income and we do it gross.

19:51.162 --> 19:57.394
Some people do it after, they do it net of paying their pension and paying their tax and all that.

19:58.178 --> 19:59.960
That's absolutely fine, people can do that.

19:59.980 --> 20:06.228
The reason why we go for gross is because we want God to get the first bit, not the second bit, after the tax and the pensions.

20:06.488 --> 20:17.262
So we get the amount we earn across the year and then all we do is take what is 10% of that and divide it by 12 so that we have a monthly amount that we give.

20:17.662 --> 20:19.605
It says simple as that.

20:20.126 --> 20:26.834
I say it's simple and it's easy, it's easy-ish, perhaps it's not easy at all, particularly if we're new to it.

20:27.490 --> 20:30.154
because it can look terrifying and impossible to do that.

20:30.474 --> 20:32.838
Pete, I hear what you're saying, but I couldn't possibly do that.

20:32.898 --> 20:36.263
I get that because we all live to the means we have, don't we?

20:36.904 --> 20:41.971
If you get a pay rise of 1,000 pounds this year, you don't get to the end of the year and find, oh, I've got 1,000 pounds in my bank.

20:42.252 --> 20:42.752
Of course not.

20:43.033 --> 20:44.154
We live to the means.

20:44.214 --> 20:51.004
We expand our spending and what we invest into and what we do with our money and our holidays we have and all that stuff based on what we have.

20:51.285 --> 20:54.930
So starting this process can be really tough.

20:55.842 --> 20:58.444
It's actually easier if we don't have much.

20:58.565 --> 21:08.434
If you've got 20 quid, bringing two pounds of it is much easier than having 50,000 and thinking, hold on, that means I need to divide 5,000 pounds by 12.

21:08.494 --> 21:09.215
Hold on, what's that?

21:09.235 --> 21:12.578
It's about 400 and help me say 110 ish.

21:12.598 --> 21:13.859
I don't know, something like that a month.

21:15.040 --> 21:18.143
That might be harder for us to step into.

21:18.303 --> 21:21.466
And we can step into it gradually if that's what we feel God is saying.

21:22.507 --> 21:23.268
But it's worth it.

21:24.229 --> 21:25.490
It's easy to step in.

21:25.986 --> 21:29.773
When you have a little, it's harder if you have a lot.

21:30.875 --> 21:39.211
That's why at this, the man's face fell and he went away sad for he had many possessions.

21:39.231 --> 21:47.346
If he only had a bunny rabbit, he could have sold it and given the money to the poor and carried on following Jesus, but he had a lot and so it was harder.

21:48.578 --> 21:51.823
Now, some people might say that this stuff, this tithing thing, well, this is outdated.

21:52.244 --> 21:53.406
It's Old Testament law.

21:53.666 --> 21:59.936
But remember, it did start before the law was written and it came out of hearts filled with gratitude and praise.

22:00.257 --> 22:13.618
And Jesus himself, when he had an opportunity to say, you don't need to tithe anymore because he was telling the Pharisees off in Matthew 23, he said this, he said, look guys, you're tithing on these different things.

22:13.954 --> 22:19.225
But you've forgotten the more important things of justice and mercy and faithfulness.

22:20.427 --> 22:23.273
And then he doesn't say, don't bother with tithing anymore.

22:23.673 --> 22:25.056
You need to just do those three.

22:25.096 --> 22:34.034
He said, you should have practiced the latter justice, mercy and faithfulness without neglecting the former tithing.

22:35.490 --> 22:37.793
So he had a chance to say, can't tithing is no more.

22:38.114 --> 22:41.499
But actually, he was saying you should be tithing, but don't forget the other things of the kingdom too.

22:41.559 --> 22:43.382
It's not, don't just be religious with your money.

22:43.943 --> 22:46.406
Make sure that you give me your whole heart.

22:49.250 --> 22:49.791
Okay.

22:49.811 --> 22:50.652
Well, there's tithing.

22:50.672 --> 22:51.454
Hopefully that's helpful.

22:51.774 --> 22:55.900
Gives you a chance to have a think, have a look, have a read, go away, have a pray and a think.

22:57.122 --> 23:01.288
Something about this church is that we don't know who tithes and who doesn't as leaders.

23:01.488 --> 23:04.213
We never look in the bank vows and say, all of this person gives that.

23:04.253 --> 23:05.234
That person gives that.

23:05.410 --> 23:06.191
Not at all.

23:06.291 --> 23:07.593
We're not going to know what you give.

23:07.673 --> 23:08.855
We're not interested in that.

23:09.176 --> 23:11.419
God is our ultimate provider when we trust Him.

23:11.840 --> 23:14.704
But we do promise to steward your gifts wisely.

23:15.325 --> 23:19.251
That is a charge that is given to us by God and we take it seriously.

23:19.892 --> 23:22.515
But don't do it because you have to, do it because you want to.

23:22.896 --> 23:34.994
I remember when I was growing up in a Bellevue Baptist, Alan Cox, when there was communion, he used to invite us to the table with this prayer, that always says, come not because you must, but because you may.

23:35.714 --> 23:36.415
That's how it began.

23:36.455 --> 23:40.399
And that's how it is with tithing.

23:40.419 --> 23:41.640
Don't do it because you feel you have to.

23:42.180 --> 23:43.782
Do it because you may and you want to.

23:44.723 --> 23:45.123
Offerings.

23:46.584 --> 23:47.125
What are offerings?

23:47.145 --> 23:51.089
Well, offerings are everything else we give that are above and beyond our tithe.

23:52.811 --> 23:58.096
And it comes from hearts being stirred and generosity being unleashed.

23:59.557 --> 24:04.722
I'm just going to pause for a brief second to, if such a thing exists, to talk about

24:05.026 --> 24:05.747
my dad.

24:06.609 --> 24:09.614
Yesterday I was at the men's breakfast and I had a really hard time.

24:09.694 --> 24:29.426
In fact it was so hard I left the breakfast and I came out here and sat on the bar over there and ate my food on my own because I didn't want to be with anybody and then I had to leave early and the reason for all of that is that yesterday marked one year of my dad passing away and we'd sailed through his birthday earlier this month and I thought I was going to be okay

24:29.890 --> 24:35.637
And then I realized, actually, I don't have loads of memories of my dad's birthday, but I have so many memories of yesterday a year ago.

24:36.318 --> 24:38.521
And every hour, I could remember different things happening.

24:39.161 --> 24:42.185
So I just want to pause and say that my dad was blooming awesome.

24:42.846 --> 24:43.887
And his legacy lives on.

24:44.568 --> 24:49.454
And I also want to say that he was one of the most generous men I ever met.

24:50.415 --> 24:52.538
His whole life, his tithes.

24:52.898 --> 24:54.180
Of course he brought his tithes.

24:54.240 --> 24:55.101
He brought his offerings.

24:55.141 --> 24:56.823
He would give wherever he could.

24:56.843 --> 24:59.186
He would sow his life out for other people.

24:59.298 --> 25:01.622
And I just want to honor him in this moment.

25:02.523 --> 25:10.615
But when it comes to offerings, thank you.

25:10.635 --> 25:18.167
When it comes to offerings, there's a beautiful moment in Exodus 35 that Nicky and I have been reading at the start of this year.

25:19.228 --> 25:22.573
And Moses has just come down the mountain from spending time with God.

25:23.194 --> 25:28.242
His face is radiant and he is carrying the two stone tablets on which

25:28.322 --> 25:32.448
The Ten Commandments are written, and he gathers everyone together.

25:35.452 --> 25:43.324
Moses said to the whole Israelite community, this is what the Lord has commanded, from what you have, take an offering for the Lord.

25:43.624 --> 25:52.136
Everyone who is willing to bring to the Lord an offering of gold, silver, bronze, blue, purple, scarlet, yarn, fine linen, the list goes on.

25:52.517 --> 25:56.242
But I love in there everyone who is willing.

25:57.602 --> 26:02.950
Not all of you have to do this, but if your heart is moved and you're willing, then bring it.

26:03.991 --> 26:06.255
Give this amazing offering.

26:07.196 --> 26:24.562
Then the whole Israelite community withdrew from Moses' presence and everyone who was willing and whose heart moved them came and brought an offering to the Lord for the work on the tent of meeting for all its service and for the sacred garments, all who were willing

26:24.994 --> 26:31.124
Men and women alike came and brought gold, jewelry of all kinds, brooches, earrings, rings and ornaments.

26:32.386 --> 26:33.608
All who were willing.

26:35.431 --> 26:40.579
All the Israelite men and women who were willing brought to the Lord free will offerings.

26:41.040 --> 26:44.946
For all the work the Lord through Moses had commanded them to do.

26:45.442 --> 26:58.460
This was gonna pay for the work that God had commanded them to do, and we have a free will offering next week, an opportunity to give an offering to ensure that we can keep doing the things that God is calling us to do.

26:58.480 --> 27:05.990
We don't find ourselves, because of the cost of living crisis and all of things, we don't find ourselves in a financially flush situation.

27:06.471 --> 27:12.119
We actually lost about 25,000 last year, and we could only do that for three years before we had nothing.

27:12.499 --> 27:14.642
We are in a situation.

27:14.722 --> 27:16.785
where we are looking to God and trusting God.

27:16.826 --> 27:22.014
But although we do all this stuff, please don't think that we are a rich organization.

27:22.315 --> 27:24.498
We actually want to lift our heads.

27:25.420 --> 27:28.705
Hear what God is asking us to do and crack on with it.

27:29.427 --> 27:31.210
Trusting that the money will follow.

27:31.230 --> 27:38.462
What we never want to be is a church that looks at the spreadsheet and says we can only do A, B and C. That's boring.

27:39.023 --> 27:41.106
We've got a thing on our wall upstairs.

27:41.634 --> 27:45.499
that says, always leave room for God to do a miracle.

27:45.519 --> 27:46.941
And that's what we're going to do as a church.

27:46.981 --> 27:48.483
We're going to hear what He asks us to do.

27:48.563 --> 27:49.504
We're going to crack on.

27:50.305 --> 27:55.772
But everybody who was willing had an opportunity here to bring their free will offering.

27:56.373 --> 28:00.779
Skilled workers who were doing all the work on the sanctuary left what they were doing.

28:00.799 --> 28:02.661
This is great this bit.

28:02.681 --> 28:06.887
And said to Moses, the people are bringing more than enough for doing the work.

28:06.987 --> 28:08.429
The Lord commanded to be done.

28:08.449 --> 28:09.330
I'd love that.

28:09.762 --> 28:11.945
Marcus has to jump up here one Sunday morning.

28:12.266 --> 28:13.347
Tell them to stop.

28:13.968 --> 28:15.330
We've got more than enough.

28:15.650 --> 28:16.952
We don't know what to do with it.

28:17.212 --> 28:18.594
I mean, that's actually what happens here.

28:18.634 --> 28:21.719
Then Moses gave an order and they sent this word throughout the camp.

28:22.099 --> 28:25.885
No man or woman is to make anything else as an offering for the sanctuary.

28:26.425 --> 28:33.575
And so the people were estranged from bringing more because what they already had was more than enough to do the work.

28:34.056 --> 28:35.498
That would be a cool place to get to.

28:35.578 --> 28:36.760
We'd all be loving that.

28:37.341 --> 28:38.322
That would be amazing.

28:39.522 --> 28:45.688
Having enough to do everything God is calling us to do without worrying about what the spreadsheet says.

28:47.089 --> 28:48.931
So, tithes, offerings.

28:49.652 --> 28:50.392
I hope that's helpful.

28:50.673 --> 28:56.919
And next week, as I said, we get our annual giving service where we can give into the ombre going vision of the church.

28:57.519 --> 29:02.584
So over this week, why don't you have a think and a pray about what you could give?

29:04.386 --> 29:08.530
In 2 Corinthians 9, it says this.

29:09.026 --> 29:21.819
Each of you should give what you have decided in your heart to give, not reluctantly or under compulsion, for God loves a cheerful giver.

29:23.120 --> 29:33.590
And God is able to bless you abundantly so that in all things, at all times, having all that you need, you will abound in every good work.

29:34.872 --> 29:37.234
I wish I put that on the slide, so I'm going to read it again.

29:38.754 --> 29:39.415
It's the one before.

29:41.178 --> 29:41.498
Thank you.

29:41.518 --> 29:42.099
I don't know what I did.

29:42.640 --> 29:43.421
You can read it again now.

29:44.122 --> 29:46.126
Because most of you were probably read it while I was talking.

29:46.386 --> 29:46.827
I didn't listen.

29:47.308 --> 29:49.291
So I always do when there's a slide behind.

29:49.331 --> 29:58.866
So each of you should give what you have decided in your heart to give, not reluctantly or under compulsion for God loves a cheerful giver.

29:59.547 --> 30:06.578
And God is able to bless you abundantly so that in all things at all times, having all you need, you will abound in every good work.

30:08.418 --> 30:11.643
Now, again, I've spoken about how we do tithing.

30:12.083 --> 30:15.589
It's important that you know we also give into the offering every year.

30:16.089 --> 30:19.314
And we've made it a bit of a game when it comes to offerings.

30:19.354 --> 30:20.977
And I think some of you know the way we do it.

30:22.259 --> 30:24.903
The rule is that we both have a moment to pray.

30:25.483 --> 30:27.907
We both think about how much we should put in the offering.

30:28.288 --> 30:31.613
And then we go three, two, one, and we both say a figure.

30:32.053 --> 30:34.276
And the rule is the biggest one is what happens.

30:34.757 --> 30:38.002
And in the early stages of this fun game,

30:38.306 --> 30:39.828
I didn't find it fun at all.

30:40.288 --> 30:41.930
I thought my wife was ridiculous.

30:42.250 --> 30:43.291
She was so generous.

30:43.351 --> 30:44.352
It was so annoying.

30:46.054 --> 30:49.918
There was one time there's a fun to collect for some white goods for a family.

30:50.118 --> 30:54.723
They need a washing machine and a dishwasher or something like that.

30:54.843 --> 30:55.404
So ready?

30:55.424 --> 30:56.365
Three, two, one.

30:56.405 --> 30:57.907
I'm like 50 pounds.

30:57.927 --> 31:00.069
Nicki's like, we need to buy it all.

31:01.450 --> 31:01.871
What do you mean?

31:02.111 --> 31:04.474
We're just going to take them to Currys and buy the lot.

31:04.494 --> 31:04.914
No.

31:05.730 --> 31:06.711
Well, how can that be fair?

31:06.731 --> 31:07.612
50 quid was good.

31:07.652 --> 31:09.133
You were supposed to say 60.

31:09.914 --> 31:10.755
We could have agreed on that.

31:11.115 --> 31:16.760
So there's been loads of times over the years when we've played this game, and I was notoriously low, wasn't I?

31:17.301 --> 31:18.742
I'd be like, OK, 100.

31:18.862 --> 31:19.783
She's like 300.

31:20.444 --> 31:20.724
Done it.

31:21.285 --> 31:21.865
I lost it again.

31:21.905 --> 31:22.606
But it's cool.

31:23.126 --> 31:24.308
And it was fun for us.

31:24.328 --> 31:28.251
I'm not suggesting you do that, because you should give what you've decided in your heart to give.

31:28.972 --> 31:31.194
Not the way that we do it, but how are you going to do it?

31:31.214 --> 31:33.096
Because you can make it enjoyable, and the loads are fun.

31:33.997 --> 31:35.378
Over the last few years, actually,

31:36.130 --> 31:42.318
We have, for the offering that's taking place next week, we haven't had enough money to actually give the number that we've chosen.

31:42.758 --> 31:43.299
Interesting.

31:44.240 --> 31:46.263
Word of warning, please, or word of advice.

31:46.323 --> 31:47.444
Please don't give out of debt.

31:48.365 --> 31:49.567
Next week, don't give out of debt.

31:50.748 --> 31:56.776
If you use your credit card because it gives you some points and then you pay it off for every month, you can do that.

31:56.836 --> 32:00.601
But if that gets you into debt giving you to hear, we don't need you to do that.

32:01.342 --> 32:01.983
Please don't do that.

32:02.703 --> 32:04.786
Give out of what you have, not out of what you don't have.

32:08.226 --> 32:14.234
But what we've had to do for the last few years, because we haven't had the money, is we've had to add it to our standing order of our tithe.

32:14.815 --> 32:19.260
Because you're like, oh, that figure, OK, let's divide it by 12, stick it into us, add it to our standing order.

32:19.280 --> 32:20.863
And that's just been a way that we've managed to do it.

32:21.083 --> 32:22.425
There's loads of ways you can do it.

32:23.005 --> 32:24.387
Have a pray, see what God might say.

32:25.569 --> 32:35.762
Over the years, we have done so much as a church through our incredible staff team who are actually our greatest resource and who aren't paid brilliantly,

32:37.666 --> 32:50.980
with our kids and youth, with our counseling and pastoral care, the things we do in and through this building that we love, we're so grateful for, the things we do out into the community, we've given money to so many great causes.

32:52.141 --> 32:53.082
Here's just an example.

32:54.043 --> 32:56.466
Some of us weren't here at the time and most of us would have forgotten.

32:56.586 --> 32:58.468
I'd forgotten until I read it and I was here.

32:58.508 --> 33:03.954
During the pandemic, we gave away prepaid shopping cards.

33:04.418 --> 33:10.768
to people from this church family and locally in the community to help, particularly with those who'd lost their jobs during the pandemic.

33:10.808 --> 33:20.163
So Tesco must have loved us because we bought prepaid shopping cards and gave them away to the tune of 35,000 pounds.

33:21.065 --> 33:25.792
I just find that phenomenal that we gave away 35,000 pounds worth of Tesco cards.

33:26.173 --> 33:31.922
And that's sort of giving it takes faith, but that's what we're about.

33:32.258 --> 33:34.782
That's the sort of generous community we are called to be.

33:34.843 --> 33:45.081
And that's why I'm unashamed this year to speak about this and to take up an annual offering for the church because we've been able to give away and to do so much.

33:45.201 --> 33:50.851
And you can be assured again that when you give, it will achieve great things because God's hand will be on it.

33:51.312 --> 33:57.202
We will never hold back from giving away from the out of the overflow of what God has given to us.

33:57.986 --> 34:03.074
anything that you give to God cannot be stolen from you in any other way.

34:03.634 --> 34:12.788
We will invest into bricks and mortar of this building that impacts so many as a church family, but we don't want to scale back the impact that we're having.

34:13.409 --> 34:20.920
We actually have vision to see this stuff increase, to see more people reach, more people bless, more hearts and lives transformed.

34:21.541 --> 34:24.445
And that's why we give into this church in particular.

34:24.485 --> 34:27.730
And that is why without cajoling, I would encourage you

34:28.194 --> 34:33.300
to do it too, not because you have to, not because you must, but because you may.

34:33.360 --> 34:37.846
Not because you have to sign on a dotted line to say you will.

34:38.867 --> 34:40.690
Bring your tithes.

34:41.190 --> 34:44.815
Give into next week's special offering because this is your home.

34:45.395 --> 34:56.529
This is where you've fed, because you believe in the cause, because you want us all to keep doing what we do and to build on it with fresh vision, with excitement for what the future holds.

34:56.549 --> 34:57.170
Let me pray.

34:59.298 --> 35:05.488
Lord, we just want to pause and thank You for everything that You have given to us.

35:09.013 --> 35:11.898
Lord, all that we have is from You.

35:14.602 --> 35:20.311
And right back in the garden, You asked us to be stewards of what You'd given to us.

35:21.994 --> 35:27.442
Help us to treat our money with good stewardship, not with ownership of its mind.

35:28.418 --> 35:29.299
but stewardship.

35:32.062 --> 35:39.130
Lord, anything that I've said this morning that isn't of you may it fall away now and be forgotten.

35:41.353 --> 35:46.078
Everything that is from you, even if it challenges, may it stick.

35:49.322 --> 35:56.370
Lord, we pray that you will come and take your place at the center of our lives, that nothing would be more valuable to us than you

35:59.458 --> 36:00.840
Lord, I pray for this church.

36:01.100 --> 36:02.923
I pray for its financial situation.

36:03.444 --> 36:12.617
Thank you that you are Jehovah Jireh, our provider, the one who meets our needs, the one that name means the one who sees and the one who sees to it.

36:13.798 --> 36:19.446
Thank you that you will see to it that everything you are calling us to will be provided for.

36:21.128 --> 36:25.074
Our eyes are on you, the author and the perfecter of our faith.

36:27.746 --> 36:30.072
Thank you God for what you're going to do in this coming year.

36:30.393 --> 36:31.595
Thank you the next January.

36:31.876 --> 36:39.976
We'll be building an amazing altar celebrating what this church did in here and out into the world.

36:41.019 --> 36:41.540
Thank you Lord.

36:41.560 --> 36:42.422
This is your church.

36:42.462 --> 36:43.144
You're building it.

36:43.204 --> 36:44.768
You love it and we love you.

36:45.309 --> 36:45.650
Amen.

